The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Wednesday, March 30, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 The CAB has sent in the names of Bengal assistant coach Satinder Singh and under-15 group B coach Rajesh Dani for Level III coaches? course from the National Cricket Academy (NCA) in Bangalore. ?Confirmation is yet to come,? a top brass CAB official said. The official revealed that they have also sent in the names of Sagarmoy Sen Sharma and Satrajit Lahiri for the Level II course. Level II course is slated to begin in the first week of April while Level III from mid April. 

 Souvik Basu will face Santanu Majumdar in the men?s singles final of the Calcutta table tennis championship on Wednesday. In the semi-finals on Tuesday, Souvik beat Amit Mukherjee 11-9, 7-11, 11-6, 11-9, 6-11, 14-12 while Santanu defeated Sangramjit Sarkar 6-11, 6-11, 11-6, 11-5, 11-5, 15-13.

 The Bankim inter-school football tournament for the Anmol-Duckback Cup will get underway on Thursday. A total of 64 schools are taking part in the 110-point meet, which will run till April 30. 

